  "prompt": "What is the best comeback when someone says \"Been there, done that\"?",
  "response": "Here are some witty comebacks for \"Been there, done that\":\n\n1. \"Cool, so you're an expert at failing?\"\n\n2. \"Congratulations on your extensive experience of mediocrity.\"\n\n3. \"Must be exhausting being so unimpressed by everything.\"\n\n4. \"Great, then you can give me some advice.\"\n\n5. \"At least I'm doing something.\"\n\n6. \"So why aren't you doing it better now?\"\n\n7. \"Thanks for the input, professional been-there-er.\"\n\n8. \"Sounds like you've mastered the art of not trying.\"\n\n9. \"And yet, here you are, still talking about it.\"\n\n10. \"Glad to see you're an expert at past tense.\"\n\nThe best comeback depends on the context, your relationship with the person, and the tone you want to set. Sometimes a humorous response works best, while other times a more direct or serious approach might be more effective.",
